verbs.description: unberth (third-person singular simple present unberths, present participle unberthing, simple past and past participle unberthed)

definitionGroups.group: (transitive) To bring (a ship etc.) out of its berth.

entries.meaning: (astronautics) To remove a spaceship from a dock/berth/mount/mooring with the assistance of a device that moves the spaceship away from its fixed location.
